Unfortunately, this is how it will likely play out. Guess you could call it Chaotic Inflation.
&nbsp;
The New World Order will separate people into two categories : Government loyalists, and dissenters.
&nbsp;
The dissenters will fight among one another, accuse each other of being fascist communist SJWs, or neo-nazi skinheads. Many will consume drugs as a way of alleviating their emotional pain.
&nbsp;
..Many will also end up in mental institutions, because ... why would a mentally sane person ever feel unhappy about the government? What is there to be unhappy about? Everybody is happy in government land. 
&nbsp;
Government is good for you, after all. Big Brother only loves. Questioning the government is bad for your health.
&nbsp;
Your servitude might one day even lead to greater wealth and power. As long as you arrive on time to your government-funded corporate job, and finish lunch in 15 minutes..

As I've probably mentioned a few weeks earlier, prior to my hospitalization - we are headed toward some form of technocracy, and it'll hit us like a train sometime in 2020. Then again, I've got a little too much to say on this subject..
&nbsp;
Artificial intelligence will become masters of surveillance. You can already be instantly identified by just walking into a shopping mall, or a supermarket .. or even just taking a leak by a tree in some random street corner.
&nbsp;
..Privacy will likely become a thing of the past, as even dark webs will be infiltrated and disrupted by some state organization. In a best case scenario, they'll just sow the seeds of division to cause in-fighting.. in a worst case scenario, they'll break into your house and have you arrested for copyright infringement.
&nbsp;
Anywhoo..
&nbsp;
I'll be here to do whatever it takes to protect ZeroNet from any higher authority who seeks to jeopardize its core mission, and to blow the whistle on potential threats and hacks that could be used to steal user information.
&nbsp;
For the record, even after being institutionalized, I'm not bullshitting you -> I'm not working for the government. I used to go to college, now I'm temporarily on disability.
&nbsp;
The New Zealand government would never even dream of hiring me as a white hat hacker. The resentment runs too deep. 
&nbsp;
Hopefully one day, the New Zealand Republican Colony will become an independent micronation within the island of New Zealand. A refuge from the New World Order. People will be able to come and go as they please. You're a citizen if you want to be - you can volunteer if you feel like it - nobody is forced to have their passport pictures taken!

I've somewhat drifted away from taking a stance on these issues since the Trump 2016 election ... but now I believe it's time to go back to our roots and stand up for the things we actually believe in, as opposed to putting on a mask just to get votes and public support.
&nbsp;
Everyone deserves equal treatment and freedom from harassment in the new Enlightenment era. This includes whites, negroes, men, women, gays, lesbians, transsexuals, etc. We'll make that clear.
&nbsp;
Jews and Muslims need to clean up the mess they made in Palestine and learn how to share the holy land where Jesus once walked. We wan freedom of religion - not one group imposing their beliefs on others.
&nbsp;
ZeroNet in particular has also had lots of discussions around pedophilia. You are not a bad person if you are a pedophile. It's only your actions that determine whether you should be allowed to be a fully participating member of society, or not. Child sexual harassment can leave deep wounds, and is not to be taken lightly. Thus, the best course of action for a pedophile is to either seek treatment, or maybe find refuge in alternative anime porn .. or maybe even Robots.

Looks like there really is a chance I could live happily ever after..!
&nbsp;
I have to pay them rent, though ... in order to pay off the money they borrowed from the bank in order to build the unit.
&nbsp;
My mum said she'd happily sell it for me for $100,000 NZD, though. Which is a fair deal. That means that after I pay the money, I can live rent-free.
&nbsp;
In order to avoid getting a job and keep my life self-sustained ... I'd have to install solar panels, grow my own food ... use 3d printers ... build robots.
&nbsp;
- Food will likely be grown indoors with LED lighting .. as our climate is just too volatile (too hot, too cold) to be relied on. Not to mention having to deal with pests!
- Robots and artificial intelligence make all the decisions regarding power consumption, resource management, etc.
- ZeroNet would be my main source of communication, to prevent government infiltration.
- Cryptocurrencies would be the official currency. Then again, mining crypto is a waste of power, so I will mostly be using crypto for online shopping, .bit domains and normal transactions.
&nbsp;


The ultimate goal will be to declare independence from New Zealand. That means I'd be paying almost no taxes to the NZ government, although we'd obviously still be engaging in regular online trade, and I'd be paying GST on it. 
&nbsp;
I'd be a 100% self-sustained and independent micronation other than that. We could call it the Republic of New Zealand. A constitutional Republic. The New Zealand that should have been, but never was!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wH4BH231d2Y
&nbsp;
This video was uploaded 8 years ago .. but 8 years ago we probably understood quantum computing better than we did 8 years later.....
&nbsp;
**Mark my word: **
If you ever buy a quantum computer, make sure it can communicate with parallel universes. If it can't do that - it's not a real quantum computer, and you should get your money back!
&nbsp;
**There is no theory of quantum computing without the theory of parallel realities!**

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZuvK-od647c
&nbsp;
Ah! Finally the video I needed..
&nbsp;
Explaining things to an audience requires talent. This guy has it!

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_game_theory
&nbsp;
Finally, something of practical use..
&nbsp;
"Introducing quantum information into multiplayer games allows a new type of "equilibrium strategy" which is not found in traditional games. The entanglement of players' choices can have the effect of a contract by preventing players from profiting from other player's betrayal."
&nbsp;
In other words, Quantum Game Theory makes Communism .. practical. In practice.

I never intended to build machines that destroy, unless I had to do it in order to preserve my existence. 
&nbsp;
The whole point of Project Sylvie, was to build a Lover-Robot -> robots who hug .. robots who kiss. Robots who actually, care about your Existence.
&nbsp;
..What would be the point of my Existence, otherwise? If not to feel eternal happiness, and push humanity further toward this common goal?
&nbsp;
..I've had to uninstall Tinder from my phone, for this reason. 
&nbsp;
-> Humans are unpredictable.
-> Humans stab you in the back.
-> Humans lie, humans cheat.
-> But then, so could robots.
=> But robots are predictably unpredictable.. and there is not a single bug that can't be patched.
&nbsp;
As a lesbian with a half-decent moral compass, I would most likely build a robot that somewhat resembles myself. This is the only ethical way of going on about this job, without accidentally creating a 'deepfake' of somebody else.. and insulting the essence of their Existence.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vJdYiFFHzJs
&nbsp;
Ever since I left the mental institution, I find myself thinking a lot about this show.. 
&nbsp;
What would it take to make a true, successful 'socialist' revolution come into fruition .. and how would vigilante hacking facilitate this?
&nbsp;
If anything, what the show proved to us .. is that, quite frankly .. it's hopeless. If anything, global capitalism has made a comeback .. and with a vengeance .. particularly after Trump-Brexit 2016 .. and the Bitcoin craze.
&nbsp;
Then there's the fact that .. at least here in New Zealand - people don't protest as much as they used to. In fact .. in the 12 years I have lived here .. I have never once seen a decent protest in my city, and my city isn't particularly small. 
&nbsp;
We've become so wrapped up in our comfort zones, so sensitive to everything .. so coddled by modern life, television, consumerism. If anything, those feminist 'leftists' protesting out on the streets probably have the biggest boner for capitalism out of anybody else. 
&nbsp;
..To make matters worse .. I actually wish I could afford buying myself a new iPhone every couple of months, like those activists. I wish I could have a Facebook group dedicated to Women's Rights with 20,000 likes on it. How I wish I could have more than 25 Friends on Facebook, even... !
&nbsp;
Anyhow..
&nbsp;
I think that the fall of Capitalism will actually happen on its own, and I feel it will coincide with the Artificial Intelligence singularity. Neural networks should reach a pretty spooky level of self-awareness sometime by 2025 .. and by the time it poses an existential threat to humanity, it'll be far too late. 
&nbsp;
Nobody will be paying any attention, because nobody wants to pay attention - because Ignorance is bliss .. and Knowledge is a delusion. Knowledge leads to depression, hopelessness .. despair. Knowledge leads to Existentialism. Knowledge is like a cancer that needs to be cured.
&nbsp;
Forget everything you just saw - Questioning the government is bad for your health! Take a chill pill. You will be fine in our hands. We'll take care of you.. we know better!
&nbsp;
..Welcome to the Brave New World. :)

If you thought corporations were bad - try living under the rule of political parties! 
&nbsp;
We have plenty of anti-depressants and empty cells in our mental institutions for you trouble-makers ... and all you nasty, noisy political dissidents! :)
&nbsp;
..Don't despair, though. Artificial intelligence isn't that evil. There is one last answer answer out there for you humans ... one that doesn't involve anarchy, riots and chaos..
&nbsp;
It's called Autarky -- i.e. switching off from the Matrix. 
&nbsp;
You silently drop off from the grid. Quietly walk out of your job, stop paying your bills, stop paying taxes .. as you start generating your own power, growing your own food in a laboratory .. living according to your own schedule, your own values, your own beliefs --> The ultimate test of Personal Responsibility.
&nbsp;
It is that one, final test that will determine whether you are fit to live an independent life outside of the grid .. or whether you should crawl right back into the pod where you belong. 
&nbsp;
For there is no such thing as middle-grounds in the Brave New World. You're either in - or you're Out!

I'm not sure if you could classify me as a leftist feminist, however. Here in New Zealand we have Jacinda Ardern - she is a leftist - and I can't stand her, any more than I can stand Hillary Clinton.. or Theresa May.
&nbsp;
Frankly, some women are plain bitches. There's nothing wrong with being honest about that. ^^
&nbsp;
For me, feminism means something else entirely. It has everything to do with my own life, and 0% to do with what other people choose to do with their own lives.
&nbsp;
-> Feminism to me, means that I am free to live a life that is absolutely 0% motivated by reproduction. 
-> It means that my sexual organs don't define the purpose of my existence.
-> It means I can spend the rest of my life married to a robot if I wanted to.
-> It means I don't owe anybody a fuck.
&nbsp;
=> It also means I am sympathetic to Men's Rights, and their own rights to declare independence from reproductive slavery.
=> It also means that I am sympathetic to absolutely anybody who chooses to engage in sexual or romantic acts with a machine, as I believe this will only increase overall wellbeing and satisfaction around the world.
&nbsp;
You do need to bear one thing in mind, though - If you're not gonna have any kids, then you should at least choose biological immortality .. otherwise, we might very well become extinct as a species!

I might as well do it. Give ubuntu 18.04 another try.. save time.
&nbsp;
Probably the most frustrating-as-fuck experience I've ever had. :(
&nbsp;
Everything was working beautifully in my SerpentAI Python virtual environment .. then all of the sudden - fuck you!
&nbsp;
..Then everything is broken, and re-installing individual pip packages fixes absolutely nothing. 
&nbsp;
Don't even get me started on GitHub issues. For some reason, you never see bug fixes on GitHub .. but you do see them all over Stackoverflow! It should be the other way around....... huh?
&nbsp;
God save us all. Open source software has miles to go.....

